FBIS4-6776 "dreas079_c_94005" FBIS-EAS-94-079 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 North Korea U.S. Paper Cited on ROK Plans To Buy Weapons U.S. Paper Cited on ROK Plans To Buy Weapons SK2304082494 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 2200 GMT 22 Apr 94 SK2304082494 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 2200 GMT 22 Apr 94 Korean BFN [Text] According to a report in the U.S. paper THE WALL STREET JOURNAL, cited by the South Korean KBS-1 radio, the Kim Yong-sam traitorous nation-selling clique agreed with the U.S. authorities to purchase Apache offensive helicopters, anti-tank missiles, and other ultramodern weapons from the United States. The puppet authorities will soon start purchasing weapons and when these weapons are brought into South Korea, the puppet Army's arms buildup plan, pushed for by the Kim Yong-sam group under instigation of the U.S. imperialists, will be completed ahead of schedule. Reporting this, the paper revealed that the issue of purchasing U.S. military equipment was stressed during the talks between U.S. Defense Secretary Perry, who made a junket to Seoul a few days ago, and puppet high-ranking officials.
